ver issues) (download link removed as it leads to a phishing scam)\n|-\n| {{No}} || Metabooru || [[Python (programming language)|Python]] || {{proprietary}} || \n|-\n|}\n\n== Imageboards ==\n\n=== 420chan ===\nAn English-language imageboard based on [[cannabis]] culture<ref name=\"420Anon\">{{cite book |last=Olson |first=Parmy |date= |title=We Are Anonymous |url=https://books.google.de/books?id=ucE1AAAAQBAJ&pg=PT332&dq=420chan&hl=en |location= |publisher= |page= |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref> which was created on April 4, 2005 by Kirtaner Aster. The name is a reference to the larger 4chan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boingboing.net/2014/12/31/how-imageboard-culture-shaped.html|title=How imageboard culture shaped Gamergate / Boing Boing|website=boingboing.net}}</ref> and the code term ''[[420 (cannabis culture)|420]]'' of the cannabis [[subculture]]. Its boards include various drug-specific boards,<ref name=\"420Anon\" /> as well as a board featuring a [[chatbot]] named Netjester.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://taimapedia.org/index.php?title=420chan |title=Taimapedia - 420chan |last1= |first1= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 4chan ===\n{{Main|4chan}}\n4chan is an English-language imageboard based on the Japanese imageboard Futaba Channel. This imageboard is based primarily upon the posting of pictures (generally related to a wide variety of topics, from anime and popular culture to politics and sports) and their discussion. ''[[The Guardian]]'' describes it as \"at once brilliant, ridiculous and alarming.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.guardian.co.uk/news/story/0,,2266526,00.html |title=Taking the Rick &#124; News &#124; guardian.co.uk Music |author=Sean Michaels |publisher=Music.guardian.co.uk |date=2008-03-19 |accessdate=2011-09-29 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nThe site and its userbase have received attention from the media for a number of reasons, including attacks against [[Hal Turner]] on his Internet shows,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freep.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20070205/NEWS07/70205031/0/NEWS06 |title=Cyber foes find ways to silence hate-talk radio host |publisher=freep.com |accessdate=2007-02-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929115741/http://www.freep.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20070205%2FNEWS07%2F70205031%2F0%2FNEWS06 |archivedate=September 29, 2007 }}</ref> [[distributed denial-of-service attack]]s against [[eBaum's World]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vitalsecurity.org/2006/01/lindsay-lohan-causes-massive-dos-war.html |title=Lindsay Lohan causes massive DoS war |publisher=Vitalsecurity.org |date=2006-01-09 |accessdate=2008-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lelezard.com/actu/3167/ebaumsworld-assiege.html |title=Ebaumsworld assi\u00e9g\u00e9 |author=Bertiaux, Micha\u00ebl |publisher=Le L\u00e9zard |language=French |date=2006-01-09 |accessdate=2008-01-19}}</ref> taking part in [[Project Chanology]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/story.html?id=261308 |title=Online group declares war on Scientology |last=George-Cosh |first=David |work=[[National Post]] |publisher=[[CanWest Global Communications|Canwest Publishing Inc.]] |date=January 25, 2008 |accessdate=2008-01-25 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20080128145858/http://www.nationalpost.com/news/canada/story.html?id=261308 |archivedate=January 28, 2008 }}</ref> and multiple cases of [[Animal abuse|anti-animal abuse reports]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://technolog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/08/31/5010813-web-video-woman-throws-puppies-in-river-4chan-tracks-her-down?pc=25&sp=25 |title=Web video: Woman throws puppies in river, 4chan tracks her down |last=Popkin |first=Helen A.S. |work=MSNBC Technology |publisher=[[MSNBC.com]] |date=August 31, 2010 |accessdate=2010-08-31 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100910110708/http://technolog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/08/31/5010813-web-video-woman-throws-puppies-in-river-4chan-tracks-her-down?pc=25&sp=25 |archivedate=September 10, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nMany [[Internet meme]]s have originated there, including [[lolcats]],<ref>\"Lolcats' demented captions create a new Web language\", Tamara Ikenberg, ''[[The News Journal]]'', 9 July 2007</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://media.www.dailypennsylvanian.com/media/storage/paper882/news/2007/11/14/News/Iz.Not.Cats.Everywhere.Online.Trend.Spreads.Across.Campus-3099929.shtml |title=Iz not cats everywhere? Online trend spreads across campus |author=Richards, Paul |newspaper=[[The Daily Pennsylvanian]] |date=2007-11-14 |accessdate=2008-01-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071117142809/http://media.www.dailypennsylvanian.com/media/storage/paper882/news/2007/11/14/News/Iz.Not.Cats.Everywhere.Online.Trend.Spreads.Across.Campus-3099929.shtml |archivedate=2007-11-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thephoenix.com/Article.aspx?id=55486 |title=The cuteness surge |author=Steel, Sharon |newspaper=[[The Phoenix (newspaper)|The Phoenix]] |date=2008-02-01 |accessdate=2008-02-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213073432/http://thephoenix.com/Article.aspx?id=55486 |archivedate=2008-02-13 }}</ref> [[rickrolling]] and [[Pedobear]].\n\n=== 8chan ===\n{{Main|8chan}}\n8chan (or Infinitechan) was a primarily English-language imageboard, although it has sub-boards dedicated to other languages. Just like 4chan, 8chan is based on posting pictures and discussion anonymously, but unlike 4chan, 8chan lets its users decide what they want to discuss by allowing any user to create their own board dedicated to any topic, a concept first made popular by news bulletin boards like [[Reddit]]. 8chan also claims to have a strong dedication to freedom of speech and allows all content&mdash;so long as the discussion and board creation abides by United States law.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/politics/8chan-pedophiles-child-porn-gamergate/ |title=8chan, the central hive of Gamergate, is also an active pedophile network |last=Howell O'Neill |first=Patrick |work=The Daily Dot |date=November 17, 2014}}</ref> However, local moderators enforce the rules of their own boards and may delete posts as they see fit. It is currently partnered with the Japanese [[textboard]] [[2channel]].\n\n=== Futaba Channel ===\n{{Main|Futaba Channel}}\n''Futaba Channel'' (\u3075\u305f\u3070\u2606\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306d\u308b), or \"Futaba\" for short, is a popular, anonymous BBS and imageboard system based in [[Japan]]. Its boards usually do not distinguish between ''[[not safe for work]]'' and ''clean'' content, but there is a strict barrier between two-dimensional (drawn) and three-dimensional ([[computer graphics]] (CG) and photographic) pictures that is heavily enforced and debated.<ref>[http://www.2chan.net/ 2chan.net] Futaba Channel</ref>\n\n===  Hispachan ===\nHispachan was launched in November 2012<ref>[https://www.hispachan.org/historia/ Hispachan's History] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20161124120055/https://www.hispachan.org/historia/ |date=2016-11-24 }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> as a global imageboard for all Spanish-speaking countries. Unlike other image boards, Hispachan does not follow the principles of [[freedom of expression]]. [[Vice (magazine)|Vice Magazine]] describes it as \"a site for completely anonymous Spanish-language discussion that has proven popular among hackers since its launch in 2012\".<ref>[https://news.vice.com/article/this-murder-has-exposed-the-dark-side-of-mexicos-hacking-community \"This Murder Has Exposed the Dark Side of Mexico\u2019s Hacking Community\"] Vice News.</ref>\n\nIn January 2017 [[Colegio Americano del Noreste shooting|a shooting in a school]] in [[Monterrey]] (Mexico) was previously announced on Hispachan.<ref>[http://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/2017/01/19/1140708 \"Agresor en colegio de Monterrey pudo anunciar ataque en foro\"] Excelsior. {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019 [[Vice (magazine)|Vice Magazine]] accused Hispachan of being a \"collaborative misogyny\" website.<ref>[https://www.vice.com/es/article/pajwg7/hispachan-fotos-sexuales-mujeres-twitter-machismo \"Hispachan: el foro espa\u00f1ol donde se difunden im\u00e1genes sexuales de mujeres y menores sin que nadie lo impida\"] VICE Spain.</ref>\n\n=== PTchan ===\nPtchan is a Portuguese-language imageboard founded in 2010 dedicated to Portugal and Portuguese-speaking countries like Angola and Mozambique; it also contains an international section and one only for Brazilian users.\n\n=== 55chan ===\n55chan is the largest Brazilian imageboard.\n\n=== Karachan ===\nKarachan is the largest Polish imageboard at 19 million posts, founded in 2010. Karachan has received attention from the Polish media after many [[trolling]] actions targeting Polish politicians<ref>{{cite web|title=Koniec \u017cart\u00f3w z prezydenta Dudy. Policja przeszuka\u0142a mieszkanie internauty. Prokuratura wszcz\u0119\u0142a \u015bledztwo|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,75398,19542714,koniec-zartow-z-prezydenta-dudy-policja-przeszukala-mieszkanie.html|website=wyborcza.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref>, journalists<ref name=\"karaNaTemat\">{{cite web|url=http://natemat.pl/149209,hejt-na-filipa-chajzera-to-zorganizowana-akcja-karachana-sprawia-im-to-ogromna-radosc|last=\u015awiderski|first=Bartosz|work=NaTemat|title=Hejt na Filipa Chajzera to zorganizowana akcja Karachana. Sianie zam\u0119tu sprawia trollom najwi\u0119ksz\u0105 przyjemno\u015b\u0107}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tak zacz\u0119\u0142o si\u0119 obra\u017canie zmar\u0142ego syna Chajzera: \"To co, szkalujemy? ZIEJMY NIENAWI\u015aCI\u0104!\"|url=http://www.pudelek.pl/artykul/81607/tak_zaczelo_sie_obrazanie_zmarlego_syna_chajzera_to_co_szkalujemy_ziejmy_nienawiscia/|website=pudelek.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017|language=pl-PL|date=22 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hejt pod wpisem Filipa Chajzera o \u015bmierci syna to zaplanowana akcja. 'Karaczan wkracza do akcji'. A to nie wszystko|url=http://www.plotek.pl/plotek/1,138986,18400818,filip-chajzer-oglosil-na-fb-ze-stracil-syna-hejt-karaczan.html|website=plotek.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017|language=pl-PL}}</ref> and the Pope [[John Paul II]].<ref name=\"karaWyborcza\">{{cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,76842,12116040,Trolle_i_zlewy.html|last=Chmielecka|first=Julia|work=Gazeta Wyborcza|title=Trolle i zlewy}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|title=Trolling level: master. To Karachan stoi za filmikiem \"M\u00f3j s\u0105siad imigrant\"|url=http://natemat.pl/154979,trolling-level-master-to-karachan-stoi-za-filmikiem-moj-sasiad-imigrant|website=naTemat.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Scenariusz jak z horroru w Rybniku. Kto\u015b w\u0142ama\u0142 si\u0119 na konto zabitej 17-latki i straszy p\u00f3\u0142 miasta. Psychopata czy \u017cart?|url=http://damianmaliszewski.natemat.pl/229763,morderstwo-17-letniej-alicji-f-haker-podaje-alfabetem-morse-a-nazwiska-osob-zamieszanych-w-zbrodnie-thriller-w-rybniku-trwa|website=naTemat.pl|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tak wygl\u0105da\u0142a ostatnia noc Alicji|url=https://www.nowiny.pl/142151-tak-wygladala-ostatnia-noc-alicji.html?f8c520cf9300a264d96947d129db9f40=&p=3#content|website=nowiny.pl|accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref> As of July 2019 the site consists of a (Polish-language) faux page claiming the site is \"blocked\" due to \"invalid content\". However, a manual is known to exist, informing how to enter the actual forum and browse its contents.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jak wej\u015b\u0107 na Karachan|url=https://www.facebook.com/jakwejsc/photos/a.1602552680000935/1725491637707038/?type=1&theater|website=facebook.com/jakwejsc/|accessdate=19 October 2019|language=pl-PL|date=19 October 2019}}</ref> Its name comes from the Polish word ''karaczan'', which means a [[cockroach]], an insect that is used as Karachan's logo.\n\n=== Krautchan ===\nA primarily German-language imageboard that was founded in 2007.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Rei\u00dfmann |first1=Ole |last2=St\u00f6cker |first2=Christian |date= |title=We are Anonymous: Die Maske des Protests - Wer sie sind, was sie antreibt ... |url=https://books.google.com/?id=CkSzMbl-VsAC&pg=PT22&dq=krautchan |location= |publisher= |page=22 |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref> The name is an allusion to the [[ethnophaulism]] ''[[Kraut]]'' for Germans. Unlike most imageboards, posters on Krautchan didn't publish their postings under the generic name \"Anonymous\". The German name \"[[Bernd]]\" was used instead, and the Krautchan community identified themselves as \"Bernds\" instead of \"Anons\". In 2009, after the [[Winnenden school shooting]], the interior minister of [[Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]] cited a post on the imageboard in a press conference that appeared to forewarn of the shooting, but was later found to be fake.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/massacre-in-winnenden-school-shooting-internet-post-a-fake-a-613085.html |title=Massacre in Winnenden: School Shooting Internet Post a Fake |last=|first=|work=Spiegel Online|date=March 13, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Roth |first=Daniel |date= |title=Z\u00fcndstoff f\u00fcr den \"Columbine-Effekt\"? Die Berichterstattung \u00fcber School Shootings in deutschen Print- und Online-Medien |url=https://books.google.com/?id=A2z-uCuUkuwC&pg=PA116&dq=krautchan |location= |publisher= |page=116 |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/03/12/germany.school.shooting.women/ |title=German police now question whether killer posted warning |last=|first=|work=CNN|date=March 12, 2009}}</ref>  The site also featured a popular [[English-language]] board, /int/, which was also the origin of the [[Polandball]] [[List of Internet phenomena|internet phenomenon]] in August the same year.  On March 21, 2018 the imageboard was shut down. Two days later the imageboard ''kohlchan'' was founded as a replacement. Attempts to view the latter via Google translate are redirected to NSFW content.\n\n===2ch===\n{{Distinguish|2channel|text=[[2channel]], a japanese [[textboard]]}}\n({{Lang-ru|\u0441\u043e\u0441\u0430\u0447|lit=sucking chan|translit=sos\u00e1ch}}, also known as '''Dvach''', {{Lang-ru|\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0447|lit=|translit=dv\u00e1ch}})<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://lurkmore.to/%D0%94%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%87|script-title=ru:\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447|work=Lurkmore|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru}}</ref> is Russian imageboard which was created as result of shut down of the 2ch.ru (originally known as dvach) occurred on January 17, 2009; it thoroughly copied original [[Page layout|layout]] and was heavily advertised over the internet and succeeded original in popularity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lurkmore.to/%D0%93%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%8B_%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%B5%D1%87%D0%B0|title=\u0413\u0435\u0442\u044b 2ch.hk|website=Lurkmore}}</ref> According to its owners number of posts left in the /b/ board exceeded 150 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://2ch.hk/b/arch/2017-03-31/res/150010363.html|title=//\u0411/\u0440\u0435\u0434/ - \u0447\u0435 \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e \u0432 |website=\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447}}</ref> In September 2016 a pro-Russian government organisation [[Mail.Ru|MAIL.RU]] helped to organize \"defense\" against alleged DDOS attacks that took place during the same month; events raised concerns and speculations among users who grew suspicious over alleged takeover committed by the mail.ru and who criticized owner's controversial decision to accept \"help\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://lurkmore.to/2ch.hk#2ch.mail.ru|title=2ch.hk|work=Lurkmore|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://meduza.io/news/2016/09/30/mail-ru-zaschitila-dvach-ot-ddos-ataki|title=Mail.ru \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \"\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447\" \u043e\u0442 DDoS-\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438|work=Meduza|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://wiki.1chan.ca/%D0%A1%D0%BE%D1%81%D0%B0%D1%87|script-title=ru:\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0430\u0447 \u2014 \u041a\u043e\u043b\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0438\u043a\u0438|website=wiki.1chan.ca|language=ru|access-date=2018-10-08}}</ref> As of October 2018 It was widely believed that imageboard was simply \"sold\" on undisclosed terms to pro-government organisation.<ref name=\":0\" /> The decision was met with high criticism of risks of [[Privacy|disclosure]] of users' credentials in inherently anonymous-community to the government body that could potentially violate principles of anonymity urging many to leave the board by the end of 2016. In October 2018 users from Dvach disclosed true identity of one of suspects who was allegedly involved in [[Poisoning of Sergei and Yulia Skripal|poisoning of ex-Russian spy]] and other British subjects in [[Salisbury|Salisbery]]. Users from dvach emailed several [[Bellingcat]] investigators to whom they provided public photos of him showing his real name on board of honorably awarded military serviceman and his participation in public events in Russian {{Ill|\u0414\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0435\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435|ru||lt=Far Eastern High General Military Command Academy|WD=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meduza.io/en/brief/2018/10/03/the-real-russia-today|title=The Real Russia. Today. Chepiga's damn photos|website=meduza.io|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/salisbury-novichok-suspect-spotted-picture-13351013|title=Salisbury Novichok suspect 'spotted in picture at Russian military academy'|last=Stewart|first=Will|date=2018-10-03|website=mirror|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AricToler/status/1047174952372371456|title=The folks at Dvach (Russian 4chan-ish site) found a lot of Chepiga stuff too, ...|last=Toler|first=Aric|date=2018-10-02|website=@AricToler|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10|quote=The folks at Dvach (Russian 4chan-ish site) found a lot of Chepiga stuff too, apparently. We didn't know about their findings before we published our new article. This one may show Chepiga at a DVOKU event}}</ref> By 2019 it remains among the largest active Russian-speaking imageboards.\n\n=== Wizardchan ===\nWizardchan is an imageboard primarily dedicated to male virgin culture and topics including anime, hobbies, and depression. Users on the depression board often discuss [[suicide]] or [[self-harm]], and a controversy emerged in the board's community about whether to refer users to [[crisis hotline|suicide prevention hotlines]].<ref name=\"slateWizards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/users/2015/03/reddit_and_suicide_intervention_how_social_media_is_changing_the_cry_for.html|last=Hess|first=Amanda|work=Slate|title=Please Do Not Downvote Anyone Who\u2019s Asked for Help}}</ref>\n\n=== Ylilauta ===\n{{Main|Ylilauta}}\nYlilauta is a Finnish-language imageboard that was founded in 2011 with the merger of the two most popular Finnish imageboards, Kotilauta and Lauta.net.{{Citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Anonymous (group)]]\n* [[Textboard]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://tanami.org/overscript/ Overscript] - a list of imageboard software\n* [http://allchans.org/ AllChans - OverChan V.3] - a list of imageboards\n\n{{Anonymous and the Internet}}\n{{Internet slang}}\n\n[[Category:Internet forum terminology]]\n[[Category:Internet culture]]\n[[Category:Internet forums]]\n[[Category:Virtual communities|*]]\n[[Category:Imageboards| ]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:4chan.png|Screenshot from the [[4chan]].org imageboard.|thumb|right|250px]]\nAn '''imageboard''' is a type of [[Internet forum]] that revolves around the posting of images, often alongside related text and discussion. The first imageboards were created in [[Japan]] as an extension of the [[textboard]] concept. These sites later inspired the creation of a number of [[English language|English-language]] imageboards, such as [[4chan]].\n\n== Characteristics ==\nImageboards, similar to [[bulletin board system]]s, are used for discussions of a variety of topics. The primary focus of imageboards, however, is directed away from text posts, and is instead placed on picture posts. The two share many of the same structures, including separate forums for separate topics, as well as similar audiences. Imageboards are much more transitory with content\u2014on some boards (especially highly trafficked ones), the thread deletion time can be as little as 10 minutes. In [[Japan]], where imageboards are more common{{citation needed|reason=Needs proof not just assumption|date=April 2016}}, topics will vary widely, ranging from [[train]]s to current [[news]]. The most popular [[English language]] imageboard, [[4chan]], similarly has a large  variety of topics.\n\nImageboards are also different from [[image hosting service|online galleries]] in that most of the works posted are not made by the poster, but instead are taken from other online sources: galleries, other imageboards, and edited pictures.\n\n=== Tripcodes ===\n[[File:Tripcode generation diagram.svg|thumb|right|300px|A diagram of a typical tripcode derivation process.]]\nMost imageboards and [[2channel]]-style discussion boards allow (and encourage) [[anonymous post]]ing and use a system of ''tripcodes'' instead of registration. A tripcode is the [[Hash function|hashed]] result of a password that allows one's identity to be recognized without storing any data about users. Entering a particular password will let one \"sign\" one's posts with the tripcode generated from that password, while trying to take another user's tripcode and compute their password from it (for instance, to make posts that appear to come from a particular person) is computationally difficult. For those who want a custom tripcode, however, there are custom tripcode generators (which are technically tripcode crackers) available, such as Meriken's Tripcode Engine<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/meriken/merikens-tripcode-engine-v3|title=\"Meriken's Tripcode Engine\" is a cross-platform custom tripcode generator.: meriken/merikens-tripcode-engine-v3|date=26 March 2019|publisher=|via=GitHub}}</ref> and MTY_CL.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/madsbuvi/MTY_CL|title=A custom tripcode searcher, written using OpenCL. Primarily targeting the GCN architectures (Radeon HD 77xx and later).: madsbuvi/MTY_CL|date=9 March 2019|publisher=|via=GitHub}}</ref> In general, anonymity is considered to be one of the advantages of an imageboard, and some boards have from time to time removed the ability to post with a name altogether (known as \"forced anonymous/anonymity\").\n\n== Software ==\nThere are two primary types of imageboard software packages in widespread use:{{Citation needed|date=August 2012}} linearly directed imageboards modeled closely after Futaba Channel (in which content is posted through hierarchical subsections of topical interest, usually denoted by a forward slash such as \"/f\" for female), and nonlinear imageboards modeled after [[#Danbooru-style boards|Danbooru]] (usually indicated by the usage of [[controlled vocabulary|controlled]] [[folksonomy|folksonomic]] vocabulary for topical tagging and search).\n\n=== Futaba Channel clones ===\nThere are currently several Futaba-based imageboard software packages in widespread use: ''Futallaby'', ''Wakaba'', ''Kusaba X''.\n\n''Futallaby'' is a [[PHP]] script based on the Futaba script from [[Futaba Channel]]. Although  the Futallaby source is still freely available at 1chan,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1chan.net/futallaby/ |title=Futallaby Imageboard Script |publisher=1chan.net |date= |accessdate=2011-09-29}}</ref> it is no longer in development, and the download page recommends using Wakaba instead, stating that \"Wakaba can do everything Futallaby does and so much more.\" Futallaby started as a translation of Futaba, later retooled to support XHTML and customizable CSS styles. It is mostly notable for being the first [[open source]] English imageboard script.{{Citation needed|date=August 2012}}\n\n''Wakaba'' is a [[Perl]] imageboard script with a SQL backend to store thread information.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wakaba.c3.cx |title=wakaba.c3.cx |publisher=wakaba.c3.cx |date= |accessdate=2011-09-29}}</ref> It is designed to be more efficient and cleanly written than other scripts that are available, while preserving the same kind of functionality. Wakaba is one of the most popular western imageboard software scripts,{{Citation needed|date=August 2012}} used most notably by iichan (''Wakachan'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wakachan.org/ |title=wakachan.org |publisher=wakachan.org |date= |accessdate=2011-09-29}}</ref> Because of its focus on bare-bones functionality, Wakaba lacks many of the modern amenities provided by 4chan's Yotsuba,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.4chan.org/news?all#108 |title=4chan Inline Extension News Post}}</ref> and newer imageboard scripts. A few users have attempted to remedy this by [[Fork (software development)|forking]] the original project and adding in features they consider beneficial. Two [[FOSS]] examples of this are frankusr's Wakaba fork,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/frankusrs/Wakaba |title=frankusr's Wakaba Fork Repository}}</ref> and the user experience focused ''Glaukaba''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/marlencrabapple/Glaukaba |title=Glaukaba Imageboard Script}}</ref>\n\n''Kusaba'' was a modular imageboard software written in PHP, which used [[MySQL]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/tslocum/kusaba |title=Kusaba Imageboard Script |author=tslocum |publisher=GitHub |date= |accessdate=2013-06-06}}</ref> The creator has discontinued the project, however, and recommends TinyIB instead.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n\n''Kusaba X'' is a continuation of Kusaba. Like Kusaba, Kusaba X is written in PHP, and is designed with modularity in mind. It requires a [[MySQL]] or [[SQLite]] database to run. Kusaba and its derivatives were at one time some of the most popular imageboard solutions.{{Citation needed|date=August 2012}} Kusaba X has since fallen out of active development, and has not been updated since July 2011.\n\n''Tinyboard'' is a PHP based imageboard script with a MySQL backend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/savetheinternet/Tinyboard |title=Tinyboard - The better imageboard software |author=savetheinternet |publisher=GitHub |date= |accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> It was eventually discontinued and forked into ''vichan'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/vichan-devel/vichan |title=vichan - Tinyboard branch taking lightweightness somewhat more liberally |author=czaks |publisher=GitHub |date= |accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> which itself was forked into ''infinity''<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://github.com/ctrlcctrlv/infinity |title=infinity - A vichan fork permitting users to create their own boards |author=ctrlcctrlv |publisher=GitHub |date= |accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> and later ''infinity'' was forked into ''OpenIB.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/OpenIB/OpenIB |title=OpenIB - An infinity fork focused on security. |author=Cipherwraith |publisher=GitHub |date= |accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> Tinyboard (and its forks) notably feature extensibility with JavaScript<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/vichan-devel/vichan/issues/252 |title=Cool codes js to improve vichan? #252 |accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> and the infinity and OpenIB forks include user-submitted board creation.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n''Lynxchan'' is an imageboard based on [[JavaScript]] and [[Node.js]]. It requires a [[MongoDB]] database to run.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gitgud.io/LynxChan/LynxChan |title=LynxChan - The best chan engine that you will ever shitpost with.  |author=Stephen Lynx |publisher=GitGud |date= |accessdate=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n''sukiyaki'' A futaba-style imageboard script that doesn't require a database.\n[[PHP]]<ref>https://github.com/iyra/sukiyaki sukiyaki </ref>\n\n''shittyboard'' is a small imageboard script that doesn't require a database (uses CSV-like file in order to store posts) and provides unique captcha, that can filter out not only bots, but also people, who don't know anything about the topic and don't want to educate themselves. It is best suited for low-traffic use-cases, and it comes pre-configured, which makes installing this script super easy. Works perfectly with older web-browsers.\n[[PHP]]<ref>https://github.com/shittyboard/shittyboard</ref>\n\n=== Danbooru-style boards ===\n\nUsually referred to as a \"[[wikt:booru|booru]]\" (plural \"boorus\"). Unlike Futaba-inspired imageboard software packages, Danbooru and derivatives aim for a non-hierarchical semantic structure in which users are able to post content and add [[tag (metadata)|tag]]s, annotations, translations, artist commentary, and comments.\n\nThere exist a number of different Danbooru-style imageboards, both those with shared source code and those that are not released for others to use. The two main Danbooru derivatives are Gelbooru and MyImouto.\n<!--\nSome imageboard engines have a public API which can be used to automate publication and post viewing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gelbooru.com/index.php?page=help&topic=dapi |title=Gelbooru |publisher=Gelbooru |date= |accessdate=2011-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://danbooru.donmai.us/help/api |title=Danbooru |publisher=Danbooru.donmai.us |date= |accessdate=2011-09-16}}</ref> A de facto standard for the API, created by Danbooru and used by the other imageboards has been established for this. The feature is used by a number of board crawlers<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibsearch.i-forge.net/ |title=Imageboards Searcher |publisher=I-forge.net |date= |accessdate=2011-09-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tenshichan.com/ |title=Safe Imageboards Search Engine |publisher=Tenshichan.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-04}}</ref> and Firefox extensions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/danbooru/ |title=danbooru :: Add-ons for Firefox |last=Hayashime |first=Atachi |publisher=Addons.mozilla.org |date=2007-03-25 |accessdate=2011-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://danbooru.donmai.us/help/extension |title=Danbooru |publisher=Danbooru.donmai.us |date= |accessdate=2011-09-16}}</ref>\n-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Traits of Danbooru-style imageboards\n! Shared !! Software !! Programmed in !! License !! Notes\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/r888888888/danbooru Danbooru] || [[Ruby on Rails]] || {{free|[[FreeBSD License#2-clause license .28.22Simplified BSD License.22 or .22FreeBSD License.22.29|FreeBSD]]}} || Uses [[PostgreSQL]].<ref>From [https://github.com/r888888888/danbooru/blob/master/README Readme]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} of the source code.</ref>\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [http://code.shishnet.org/shimmie2/ Shimmie 2] || [[PHP]] || {{free|[[GPL#Version 2|GPLv2]]}} || Uses [[MySQL]] by default (as part of LAMP), can also use PostgreSQL.\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/digiwombat/naranai naranai 1.3.x] || [[PHP]] || {{free|[[GPL#Version 3|GPLv3]]}} || Uses MySQL. Built to replace Danbooru because author considered Ruby unsuitable.<ref>From [https://github.com/digiwombat/naranai/blob/master/README Readme] of the source code.</ref>\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/rr-/szurubooru szurubooru] || [[Python (programming language)|Python]] || {{free|[[GPL#Version 3|GPLv3]]}} || Uses PostgreSQL.\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/moebooru/moebooru Moebooru] || [[Ruby on Rails]] || {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}} || Uses PostgreSQL.\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://code.acr.moe/kazari/myimouto-untouched MyImouto] || [[PHP]] || {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}} || Uses MySQL. PHP port of Moebooru. Uses a custom Ruby-on-Rails-like framework.<ref>From [https://code.acr.moe/kazari/myimouto-untouched/blob/master/README.md Readme] of the source code.</ref>\n|-\n| {{Yes}} ||[https://chan.sankakucomplex.com/ Sankakucomplex] ||[[PHP]]|| {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}} ||Uses PostgreSQL.\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://code.acr.moe/kazari/sequenzia Sequenzia] || [[PHP]] || {{free|[[MIT License|MIT]]}} || Uses MySQL. Modified and re-designed port of MyImouto for the [https://web.archive.org/web/20190103033729/http://sequenzia.acr.moe/ Sequenzia Project].<ref>From [https://acr.moe/index.php/Sequenzia_Project Sequenzia Project] Wiki page.</ref> Some code is specialised for the Sequenzia Project and AC Research.<ref>From [https://code.acr.moe/kazari/sequenzia/blob/master/README.md Readme] of the source.</ref>\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/derpibooru/philomena Philomena] || [[Elixir (programming language)|Elixir]]|| {{free|[[Affero General Public License|AGPLv3]]}} || Uses PostgreSQL, [[Elasticsearch]] and the [[Phoenix (web framework)|Phoenix Framework]]. Successor to booru-on-rails.\n|-\n| {{Yes}} || [https://github.com/derpibooru/booru-on-rails booru-on-rails] || [[Ruby on Rails]] || {{free|[[Affero General Public License|AGPLv3]]}} || Uses PostgreSQL, used to use MongoDB. Has been superseded by  [https://github.com/derpibooru/philomena Philomena] and is no longer actively developed as of December 2019.\n|-\n| {{No}} || [https://gelbooru.com/index.php?page=forum&s=view&id=99 Gelbooru 0.2.x] || [[PHP]] || {{proprietary}} || Uses MySQL. Gelbooru 0.1.x is open source but 0.2.x currently is not.\n|-\n| {{No}} || Octabooru || [[PHP]] || {{proprietary}} || (temporarily down due to host server issues) (download link removed as it leads to a phishing scam)\n|-\n| {{No}} || Metabooru || [[Python (programming language)|Python]] || {{proprietary}} || \n|-\n|}\n\n== Imageboards ==\n\n=== 420chan ===\nAn English-language imageboard based on [[cannabis]] culture<ref name=\"420Anon\">{{cite book |last=Olson |first=Parmy |date= |title=We Are Anonymous |url=https://books.google.de/books?id=ucE1AAAAQBAJ&pg=PT332&dq=420chan&hl=en |location= |publisher= |page= |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref> which was created on April 4, 2005 by Kirtaner Aster. The name is a reference to the larger 4chan<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boingboing.net/2014/12/31/how-imageboard-culture-shaped.html|title=How imageboard culture shaped Gamergate / Boing Boing|website=boingboing.net}}</ref> and the code term ''[[420 (cannabis culture)|420]]'' of the cannabis [[subculture]]. Its boards include various drug-specific boards,<ref name=\"420Anon\" /> as well as a board featuring a [[chatbot]] named Netjester.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://taimapedia.org/index.php?title=420chan |title=Taimapedia - 420chan |last1= |first1= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 4chan ===\n{{Main|4chan}}\n4chan is an English-language imageboard based on the Japanese imageboard Futaba Channel. This imageboard is based primarily upon the posting of pictures (generally related to a wide variety of topics, from anime and popular culture to politics and sports) and their discussion. ''[[The Guardian]]'' describes it as \"at once brilliant, ridiculous and alarming.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.guardian.co.uk/news/story/0,,2266526,00.html |title=Taking the Rick &#124; News &#124; guardian.co.uk Music |author=Sean Michaels |publisher=Music.guardian.co.uk |date=2008-03-19 |accessdate=2011-09-29 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nThe site and its userbase have received attention from the media for a number of reasons, including attacks against [[Hal Turner]] on his Internet shows,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freep.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20070205/NEWS07/70205031/0/NEWS06 |title=Cyber foes find ways to silence hate-talk radio host |publisher=freep.com |accessdate=2007-02-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929115741/http://www.freep.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20070205%2FNEWS07%2F70205031%2F0%2FNEWS06 |archivedate=September 29, 2007 }}</ref> [[distributed denial-of-service attack]]s against [[eBaum's World]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vitalsecurity.org/2006/01/lindsay-lohan-causes-massive-dos-war.html |title=Lindsay Lohan causes massive DoS war |publisher=Vitalsecurity.org |date=2006-01-09 |accessdate=2008-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lelezard.com/actu/3167/ebaumsworld-assiege.html |title=Ebaumsworld assi\u00e9g\u00e9 |author=Bertiaux, Micha\u00ebl |publisher=Le L\u00e9zard |language=French |date=2006-01-09 |accessdate=2008-01-19}}</ref> taking part in [[Project Chanology]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/story.html?id=261308 |title=Online group declares war on Scientology |last=George-Cosh |first=David |work=[[National Post]] |publisher=[[CanWest Global Communications|Canwest Publishing Inc.]] |date=January 25, 2008 |accessdate=2008-01-25 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20080128145858/http://www.nationalpost.com/news/canada/story.html?id=261308 |archivedate=January 28, 2008 }}</ref> and multiple cases of [[Animal abuse|anti-animal abuse reports]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://technolog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/08/31/5010813-web-video-woman-throws-puppies-in-river-4chan-tracks-her-down?pc=25&sp=25 |title=Web video: Woman throws puppies in river, 4chan tracks her down |last=Popkin |first=Helen A.S. |work=MSNBC Technology |publisher=[[MSNBC.com]] |date=August 31, 2010 |accessdate=2010-08-31 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100910110708/http://technolog.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/08/31/5010813-web-video-woman-throws-puppies-in-river-4chan-tracks-her-down?pc=25&sp=25 |archivedate=September 10, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nMany [[Internet meme]]s have originated there, including [[lolcats]],<ref>\"Lolcats' demented captions create a new Web language\", Tamara Ikenberg, ''[[The News Journal]]'', 9 July 2007</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://media.www.dailypennsylvanian.com/media/storage/paper882/news/2007/11/14/News/Iz.Not.Cats.Everywhere.Online.Trend.Spreads.Across.Campus-3099929.shtml |title=Iz not cats everywhere? Online trend spreads across campus |author=Richards, Paul |newspaper=[[The Daily Pennsylvanian]] |date=2007-11-14 |accessdate=2008-01-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071117142809/http://media.www.dailypennsylvanian.com/media/storage/paper882/news/2007/11/14/News/Iz.Not.Cats.Everywhere.Online.Trend.Spreads.Across.Campus-3099929.shtml |archivedate=2007-11-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thephoenix.com/Article.aspx?id=55486 |title=The cuteness surge |author=Steel, Sharon |newspaper=[[The Phoenix (newspaper)|The Phoenix]] |date=2008-02-01 |accessdate=2008-02-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213073432/http://thephoenix.com/Article.aspx?id=55486 |archivedate=2008-02-13 }}</ref> [[rickrolling]] and [[Pedobear]].\n\n=== 8chan ===\n{{Main|8chan}}\n8chan (or Infinitechan) was a primarily English-language imageboard, although it has sub-boards dedicated to other languages. Just like 4chan, 8chan is based on posting pictures and discussion anonymously, but unlike 4chan, 8chan lets its users decide what they want to discuss by allowing any user to create their own board dedicated to any topic, a concept first made popular by news bulletin boards like [[Reddit]]. 8chan also claims to have a strong dedication to freedom of speech and allows all content&mdash;so long as the discussion and board creation abides by United States law.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/politics/8chan-pedophiles-child-porn-gamergate/ |title=8chan, the central hive of Gamergate, is also an active pedophile network |last=Howell O'Neill |first=Patrick |work=The Daily Dot |date=November 17, 2014}}</ref> However, local moderators enforce the rules of their own boards and may delete posts as they see fit. It is currently partnered with the Japanese [[textboard]] [[2channel]].\n\n=== Futaba Channel ===\n{{Main|Futaba Channel}}\n''Futaba Channel'' (\u3075\u305f\u3070\u2606\u3061\u3083\u3093\u306d\u308b), or \"Futaba\" for short, is a popular, anonymous BBS and imageboard system based in [[Japan]]. Its boards usually do not distinguish between ''[[not safe for work]]'' and ''clean'' content, but there is a strict barrier between two-dimensional (drawn) and three-dimensional ([[computer graphics]] (CG) and photographic) pictures that is heavily enforced and debated.<ref>[http://www.2chan.net/ 2chan.net] Futaba Channel</ref>\n\n===  Hispachan ===\nHispachan was launched in November 2012<ref>[https://www.hispachan.org/historia/ Hispachan's History] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20161124120055/https://www.hispachan.org/historia/ |date=2016-11-24 }} {{in lang|es}}</ref> as a global imageboard for all Spanish-speaking countries. Unlike other image boards, Hispachan does not follow the principles of [[freedom of expression]]. [[Vice (magazine)|Vice Magazine]] describes it as \"a site for completely anonymous Spanish-language discussion that has proven popular among hackers since its launch in 2012\".<ref>[https://news.vice.com/article/this-murder-has-exposed-the-dark-side-of-mexicos-hacking-community \"This Murder Has Exposed the Dark Side of Mexico\u2019s Hacking Community\"] Vice News.</ref>\n\nIn January 2017 [[Colegio Americano del Noreste shooting|a shooting in a school]] in [[Monterrey]] (Mexico) was previously announced on Hispachan.<ref>[http://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/2017/01/19/1140708 \"Agresor en colegio de Monterrey pudo anunciar ataque en foro\"] Excelsior. {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019 [[Vice (magazine)|Vice Magazine]] accused Hispachan of being a \"collaborative misogyny\" website.<ref>[https://www.vice.com/es/article/pajwg7/hispachan-fotos-sexuales-mujeres-twitter-machismo \"Hispachan: el foro espa\u00f1ol donde se difunden im\u00e1genes sexuales de mujeres y menores sin que nadie lo impida\"] VICE Spain.</ref>\n\n=== PTchan ===\nPtchan is a Portuguese-language imageboard founded in 2010 dedicated to Portugal and Portuguese-speaking countries like Angola and Mozambique; it also contains an international section and one only for Brazilian users.\n\n=== 55chan ===\n55chan is the largest Brazilian imageboard.\n\n=== Karachan ===\nKarachan is the largest Polish imageboard at 19 million posts, founded in 2010. Karachan has received attention from the Polish media after many [[trolling]] actions targeting Polish politicians<ref>{{cite web|title=Koniec \u017cart\u00f3w z prezydenta Dudy. Policja przeszuka\u0142a mieszkanie internauty. Prokuratura wszcz\u0119\u0142a \u015bledztwo|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,75398,19542714,koniec-zartow-z-prezydenta-dudy-policja-przeszukala-mieszkanie.html|website=wyborcza.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref>, journalists<ref name=\"karaNaTemat\">{{cite web|url=http://natemat.pl/149209,hejt-na-filipa-chajzera-to-zorganizowana-akcja-karachana-sprawia-im-to-ogromna-radosc|last=\u015awiderski|first=Bartosz|work=NaTemat|title=Hejt na Filipa Chajzera to zorganizowana akcja Karachana. Sianie zam\u0119tu sprawia trollom najwi\u0119ksz\u0105 przyjemno\u015b\u0107}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tak zacz\u0119\u0142o si\u0119 obra\u017canie zmar\u0142ego syna Chajzera: \"To co, szkalujemy? ZIEJMY NIENAWI\u015aCI\u0104!\"|url=http://www.pudelek.pl/artykul/81607/tak_zaczelo_sie_obrazanie_zmarlego_syna_chajzera_to_co_szkalujemy_ziejmy_nienawiscia/|website=pudelek.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017|language=pl-PL|date=22 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hejt pod wpisem Filipa Chajzera o \u015bmierci syna to zaplanowana akcja. 'Karaczan wkracza do akcji'. A to nie wszystko|url=http://www.plotek.pl/plotek/1,138986,18400818,filip-chajzer-oglosil-na-fb-ze-stracil-syna-hejt-karaczan.html|website=plotek.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017|language=pl-PL}}</ref> and the Pope [[John Paul II]].<ref name=\"karaWyborcza\">{{cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,76842,12116040,Trolle_i_zlewy.html|last=Chmielecka|first=Julia|work=Gazeta Wyborcza|title=Trolle i zlewy}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|title=Trolling level: master. To Karachan stoi za filmikiem \"M\u00f3j s\u0105siad imigrant\"|url=http://natemat.pl/154979,trolling-level-master-to-karachan-stoi-za-filmikiem-moj-sasiad-imigrant|website=naTemat.pl|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Scenariusz jak z horroru w Rybniku. Kto\u015b w\u0142ama\u0142 si\u0119 na konto zabitej 17-latki i straszy p\u00f3\u0142 miasta. Psychopata czy \u017cart?|url=http://damianmaliszewski.natemat.pl/229763,morderstwo-17-letniej-alicji-f-haker-podaje-alfabetem-morse-a-nazwiska-osob-zamieszanych-w-zbrodnie-thriller-w-rybniku-trwa|website=naTemat.pl|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tak wygl\u0105da\u0142a ostatnia noc Alicji|url=https://www.nowiny.pl/142151-tak-wygladala-ostatnia-noc-alicji.html?f8c520cf9300a264d96947d129db9f40=&p=3#content|website=nowiny.pl|accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref> As of July 2019 the site consists of a (Polish-language) faux page claiming the site is \"blocked\" due to \"invalid content\". However, a manual is known to exist, informing how to enter the actual forum and browse its contents.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jak wej\u015b\u0107 na Karachan|url=https://www.facebook.com/jakwejsc/photos/a.1602552680000935/1725491637707038/?type=1&theater|website=facebook.com/jakwejsc/|accessdate=19 October 2019|language=pl-PL|date=19 October 2019}}</ref> Its name comes from the Polish word ''karaczan'', which means a [[cockroach]], an insect that is used as Karachan's logo.\n\n=== Krautchan ===\nA primarily German-language imageboard that was founded in 2007.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Rei\u00dfmann |first1=Ole |last2=St\u00f6cker |first2=Christian |date= |title=We are Anonymous: Die Maske des Protests - Wer sie sind, was sie antreibt ... |url=https://books.google.com/?id=CkSzMbl-VsAC&pg=PT22&dq=krautchan |location= |publisher= |page=22 |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref> The name is an allusion to the [[ethnophaulism]] ''[[Kraut]]'' for Germans. Unlike most imageboards, posters on Krautchan didn't publish their postings under the generic name \"Anonymous\". The German name \"[[Bernd]]\" was used instead, and the Krautchan community identified themselves as \"Bernds\" instead of \"Anons\". In 2009, after the [[Winnenden school shooting]], the interior minister of [[Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]] cited a post on the imageboard in a press conference that appeared to forewarn of the shooting, but was later found to be fake.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/massacre-in-winnenden-school-shooting-internet-post-a-fake-a-613085.html |title=Massacre in Winnenden: School Shooting Internet Post a Fake |last=|first=|work=Spiegel Online|date=March 13, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Roth |first=Daniel |date= |title=Z\u00fcndstoff f\u00fcr den \"Columbine-Effekt\"? Die Berichterstattung \u00fcber School Shootings in deutschen Print- und Online-Medien |url=https://books.google.com/?id=A2z-uCuUkuwC&pg=PA116&dq=krautchan |location= |publisher= |page=116 |isbn= |access-date=28 March 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2009/WORLD/europe/03/12/germany.school.shooting.women/ |title=German police now question whether killer posted warning |last=|first=|work=CNN|date=March 12, 2009}}</ref>  The site also featured a popular [[English-language]] board, /int/, which was also the origin of the [[Polandball]] [[List of Internet phenomena|internet phenomenon]] in August the same year.  On March 21, 2018 the imageboard was shut down. Two days later the imageboard ''kohlchan'' was founded as a replacement. Attempts to view the latter via Google translate are redirected to NSFW content.\n\n===2ch===\n{{Distinguish|2channel|text=[[2channel]], a japanese [[textboard]]}}\n({{Lang-ru|\u0441\u043e\u0441\u0430\u0447|lit=sucking chan|translit=sos\u00e1ch}}, also known as '''Dvach''', {{Lang-ru|\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0447|lit=|translit=dv\u00e1ch}})<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://lurkmore.to/%D0%94%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%87|script-title=ru:\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447|work=Lurkmore|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru}}</ref> is Russian imageboard which was created as result of shut down of the 2ch.ru (originally known as dvach) occurred on January 17, 2009; it thoroughly copied original [[Page layout|layout]] and was heavily advertised over the internet and succeeded original in popularity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lurkmore.to/%D0%93%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%8B_%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%B5%D1%87%D0%B0|title=\u0413\u0435\u0442\u044b 2ch.hk|website=Lurkmore}}</ref> According to its owners number of posts left in the /b/ board exceeded 150 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://2ch.hk/b/arch/2017-03-31/res/150010363.html|title=//\u0411/\u0440\u0435\u0434/ - \u0447\u0435 \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e \u0432 |website=\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447}}</ref> In September 2016 a pro-Russian government organisation [[Mail.Ru|MAIL.RU]] helped to organize \"defense\" against alleged DDOS attacks that took place during the same month; events raised concerns and speculations among users who grew suspicious over alleged takeover committed by the mail.ru and who criticized owner's controversial decision to accept \"help\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://lurkmore.to/2ch.hk#2ch.mail.ru|title=2ch.hk|work=Lurkmore|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://meduza.io/news/2016/09/30/mail-ru-zaschitila-dvach-ot-ddos-ataki|title=Mail.ru \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \"\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0447\" \u043e\u0442 DDoS-\u0430\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438|work=Meduza|access-date=2018-10-02|language=ru-RU}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://wiki.1chan.ca/%D0%A1%D0%BE%D1%81%D0%B0%D1%87|script-title=ru:\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0430\u0447 \u2014 \u041a\u043e\u043b\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0438\u043a\u0438|website=wiki.1chan.ca|language=ru|access-date=2018-10-08}}</ref> As of October 2018 It was widely believed that imageboard was simply \"sold\" on undisclosed terms to pro-government organisation.<ref name=\":0\" /> The decision was met with high criticism of risks of [[Privacy|disclosure]] of users' credentials in inherently anonymous-community to the government body that could potentially violate principles of anonymity urging many to leave the board by the end of 2016. In October 2018 users from Dvach disclosed true identity of one of suspects who was allegedly involved in [[Poisoning of Sergei and Yulia Skripal|poisoning of ex-Russian spy]] and other British subjects in [[Salisbury|Salisbery]]. Users from dvach emailed several [[Bellingcat]] investigators to whom they provided public photos of him showing his real name on board of honorably awarded military serviceman and his participation in public events in Russian {{Ill|\u0414\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0435\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435|ru||lt=Far Eastern High General Military Command Academy|WD=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meduza.io/en/brief/2018/10/03/the-real-russia-today|title=The Real Russia. Today. Chepiga's damn photos|website=meduza.io|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/salisbury-novichok-suspect-spotted-picture-13351013|title=Salisbury Novichok suspect 'spotted in picture at Russian military academy'|last=Stewart|first=Will|date=2018-10-03|website=mirror|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AricToler/status/1047174952372371456|title=The folks at Dvach (Russian 4chan-ish site) found a lot of Chepiga stuff too, ...|last=Toler|first=Aric|date=2018-10-02|website=@AricToler|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10|quote=The folks at Dvach (Russian 4chan-ish site) found a lot of Chepiga stuff too, apparently. We didn't know about their findings before we published our new article. This one may show Chepiga at a DVOKU event}}</ref> By 2019 it remains among the largest active Russian-speaking imageboards.\n\n=== Wizardchan ===\nWizardchan is an imageboard primarily dedicated to male virgin culture and topics including anime, hobbies, and depression. Users on the depression board often discuss [[suicide]] or [[self-harm]], and a controversy emerged in the board's community about whether to refer users to [[crisis hotline|suicide prevention hotlines]].<ref name=\"slateWizards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/users/2015/03/reddit_and_suicide_intervention_how_social_media_is_changing_the_cry_for.html|last=Hess|first=Amanda|work=Slate|title=Please Do Not Downvote Anyone Who\u2019s Asked for Help}}</ref>\n\n=== Ylilauta ===\n{{Main|Ylilauta}}\nYlilauta is a Finnish-language imageboard that was founded in 2011 with the merger of the two most popular Finnish imageboards, Kotilauta and Lauta.net.{{Citation needed|date=November 2018}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Anonymous (group)]]\n* [[Textboard]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://tanami.org/overscript/ Overscript] - a list of imageboard software\n* [http://allchans.org/ AllChans - OverChan V.3] - a list of imageboards\n\n{{Anonymous and the Internet}}\n{{Internet slang}}\n\n[[Category:Internet forum terminology]]\n[[Category:Internet culture]]\n[[Category:Internet forums]]\n[[Category:Virtual communities|*]]\n[[Category:Imageboards| ]]\n", "name_user": "2806:107e:14:53e:301e:d9b2:3af8:14df", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Es una p\u00e1gina de ped\u00f3filos)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imageboard"}
{"title_page": "2020 Denver Broncos season", "text_new": "{{short description|61st season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL_season\n| team            = Denver Broncos\n| logo            = Denver Broncos wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          =\n| division_place  =\n| coach           = [[Vic Fangio]]\n| owner           = Estate of [[Pat Bowlen]]\n| general manager = [[John Elway]]\n| stadium         = [[Empower Field at Mile High]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| AP All-pros     =\n| uniform         = Broncos uniforms.png<!--DO NOT place a non-free image here without complying with WP:NFCC #10c-->\n| shortnavlink    = Broncos seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Denver Broncos]]' upcoming 51st in the [[National Football League]], their 61st overall and their second under [[List of Denver Broncos head coaches|head coach]] [[Vic Fangio]]. It will also mark the team's 20th season playing their home games in their current venue, [[Empower Field at Mile High]]. The Broncos will look to improve on their 7\u20139 record from 2019 and make the playoffs for the first time since their [[2015 Denver Broncos season|2015 Super Bowl-winning season]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Coaching changes==\n*January 10: Outside linebackers coach [[Brandon Staley]] departed to become the defensive coordinator of the [[Los Angeles Rams]].<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Halloran |first=Ryan |title=Broncos OLB coach Brandon Staley to become Rams defensive coordinator, source says |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/01/10/brandon-staley-rams-defensive-coordinator/ |newspaper=The Denver Post |date=January 10, 2020 |accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 12: Offensive coordinator [[Rich Scangarello]] was fired after only one season, following a [[2019 Denver Broncos season#League rankings|2019]] season in which the Broncos ranked in the bottom five in several offensive categories, including scoring offense and total yardage. Two days later (January 14), Scangarello was replaced by [[Pat Shurmur]], who served as the [[New York Giants]]' head coach during the previous two seasons. Shurmur will become the Broncos' fifth offensive coordinator in as many seasons.<ref>{{cite web |last=DiLalla |first=Aric |title=Broncos name Pat Shurmur as offensive coordinator |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-pat-shurmur-as-offensive-coordinator |work=Denver Broncos |date=January 14, 2020 |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 15: Quarterbacks coach [[T.C. McCartney]] was fired after only one season.<ref>{{cite news |last=DiLalla |first=Aric |title=Broncos fire quarterbacks coach T.C. McCartney |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/01/15/broncos-fire-tc-mccartney/ |newspaper=The Denver Post |date=January 15, 2020 |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 28: [[Mike Shula]], who served as the Giants' offensive coordinator in 2018 and 2019 alongside Pat Shurmur, was named quarterbacks coach.<ref>{{cite web |last=Swanson |first=Ben |title=Broncos name Mike Shula as quarterbacks coach |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-mike-shula-as-quarterbacks-coach |work=Denver Broncos |date=January 28, 2020 |accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*February 6: [[John Pagano]] was named outside linebackers coach, replacing Brandon Staley. Pagano worked in the same position with the [[Houston Texans]] during the previous two seasons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Broncos name John Pagano as outside linebackers coach |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-john-pagano-as-outside-linebackers-coach |work=Denver Broncos |date=February 6, 2020 |accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Roster changes==\n===Future contracts===\nAll players listed below were signed to reserve/future contracts on December 31, 2019, unless noted otherwise. The signings include all ten players who were on the practice squad of the [[2019 Denver Broncos season#Final roster|final roster]] at the end of the 2019 season. Each player was officially added to the active roster on March 18\u2014the first day of the [[2020 NFL season|2020]] league year.<ref name=\"FutureContracts\">{{cite web |title=Broncos sign 15 players to future contracts, claim NT Joel Heath off waivers |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-sign-15-players-to-future-contracts-claim-nt-joel-heath-off-waivers |work=Denver Broncos |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Position\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Player\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Notes\n|-\n| [[Offensive tackle|OT]] || [[Ka'John Armstrong]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Wide receiver|WR]] || [[Trinity Benson]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Linebacker|LB]] || [[Malik Carney]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]] || [[Jeremy Cox]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| LB || [[Tre' Crawford]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Punter (football)|P]] || [[Trevor Daniel]] || waived April 23<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-waive-punters-colby-wadman-trevor-daniel?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook|title=Broncos waive punters Colby Wadman, Trevor Daniel|website=www.denverbroncos.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tight end|TE]] || [[Bug Howard]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| OT || [[Tyler Jones]] || signed January 15<ref>{{cite web |title=Broncos sign OL Tyler Jones to future contract |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-sign-ol-tyler-jones-to-future-contract |work=Denver Broncos |date=January 15, 2020 |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]] || [[P. J. Locke]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| WR || [[Kelvin McKnight]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Running back|RB]] || [[Khalfani Muhammad]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| S || [[Tyvis Powell]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Qua