20139 record from 2019 and make the playoffs for the first time since their [[2015 Denver Broncos season|2015 Super Bowl-winning season]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Coaching changes==\n*January 10: Outside linebackers coach [[Brandon Staley]] departed to become the defensive coordinator of the [[Los Angeles Rams]].<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Halloran |first=Ryan |title=Broncos OLB coach Brandon Staley to become Rams defensive coordinator, source says |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/01/10/brandon-staley-rams-defensive-coordinator/ |newspaper=The Denver Post |date=January 10, 2020 |accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 12: Offensive coordinator [[Rich Scangarello]] was fired after only one season, following a [[2019 Denver Broncos season#League rankings|2019]] season in which the Broncos ranked in the bottom five in several offensive categories, including scoring offense and total yardage. Two days later (January 14), Scangarello was replaced by [[Pat Shurmur]], who served as the [[New York Giants]]' head coach during the previous two seasons. Shurmur will become the Broncos' fifth offensive coordinator in as many seasons.<ref>{{cite web |last=DiLalla |first=Aric |title=Broncos name Pat Shurmur as offensive coordinator |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-pat-shurmur-as-offensive-coordinator |work=Denver Broncos |date=January 14, 2020 |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 15: Quarterbacks coach [[T.C. McCartney]] was fired after only one season.<ref>{{cite news |last=DiLalla |first=Aric |title=Broncos fire quarterbacks coach T.C. McCartney |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/01/15/broncos-fire-tc-mccartney/ |newspaper=The Denver Post |date=January 15, 2020 |accessdate=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*January 28: [[Mike Shula]], who served as the Giants' offensive coordinator in 2018 and 2019 alongside Pat Shurmur, was named quarterbacks coach.<ref>{{cite web |last=Swanson |first=Ben |title=Broncos name Mike Shula as quarterbacks coach |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-mike-shula-as-quarterbacks-coach |work=Denver Broncos |date=January 28, 2020 |accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n*February 6: [[John Pagano]] was named outside linebackers coach, replacing Brandon Staley. Pagano worked in the same position with the [[Houston Texans]] during the previous two seasons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Broncos name John Pagano as outside linebackers coach |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-name-john-pagano-as-outside-linebackers-coach |work=Denver Broncos |date=February 6, 2020 |accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Roster changes==\n===Future contracts===\nAll players listed below were signed to reserve/future contracts on December 31, 2019, unless noted otherwise. The signings include all ten players who were on the practice squad of the [[2019 Denver Broncos season#Final roster|final roster]] at the end of the 2019 season. Each player was officially added to the active roster on March 18\u2014the first day of the [[2020 NFL season|2020]] league year.<ref name=\"FutureContracts\">{{cite web |title=Broncos sign 15 players to future contracts, claim NT Joel Heath off waivers |url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-sign-15-players-to-future-contracts-claim-nt-joel-heath-off-waivers |work=Denver Broncos |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Position\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Player\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Denver Broncos|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Notes\n|-\n| [[Offensive tackle|OT]] || [[Ka'John Armstrong]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Wide receiver|WR]] || [[Trinity Benson]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Linebacker|LB]] || [[Malik Carney]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]] || [[Jeremy Cox]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| LB || [[Tre' Crawford]] || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n| [[Punter 